Me, to myself: What the actual fuck?

SC: ...but I've probably been married twice as long as you've been alive. Anyway, I won't tell you what she's into, but let's just say it ain't me. But, you're young. You'll see.

(8/?)

SC: So I told her *and he leans in real close* that I didn't like her Adkins shit and wouldn't eat it and she won't eat what I like, so we'll just need to spent more.

*pauses*

SC: So, anyway, we've been married 46 years now and it's not worth trying to kiss her anymore.

(7/?)

Me, still doesn't know: Sure, okay.

SC: *claps my shoulder again* Well, anyway, I grabbed six of those, some ice cream, some cheddar popcorn and out she comes with, "Every time you come with me it costs $30 more."

Me, to myself: Damnit.

(6/?)

Me to myself: Fuck.

SC: And she wouldn't say anything until we finally got to aisle 11 or 12, I can't remember, but you know.

Me, who doesn't know: Ice cream or bacon?

SC: *squints at me* You know! The Something-or-other bowls in the freezer!

(5/?)

SC: *turns around in his frustration and sees the jars* Well! Here there are!

Me: Well, there you go. *starts walking*

SC: *stops me* So, I was here yesterday w/ my wife & we got halfway thru the store & she stopped talking 2 me. So I says, "NOW why are you mad at me?"

(4/?)

SC: I asked one guy whose been here 25 years and he told me aisle 11. Another guy whose been here 15 told me aisle 7. 

Me: *deer in headlights nodding along* Well, I know they were in produce for a long time but they just rearranged.

(3/?)

Shoulder-clapper (SC to lend brevity) leaned in conspiratorially, & said, "So, are we having fun yet?"

Me: Um... well. Every day.

SC: I swear to God, nobody know where things r n the store anymore. *brandishes the case of mason jars* I'm just trying 2 find where these go! (2/?)

Today at the grocery store I was toodling along, minding my own business and heard behind me, "Are we having fun yet?"

Because I didn't recognize their voice and assumed they weren't talking to me, I kept on toodling along.

Then I was clapped on the shoulder. (1/?)
